from pathlib import Path
import base64, json, hashlib, gzip

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('src/experiments/toy_ising_emergent_classicality.py')
assert target_path.is_file(), 'Expected src/experiments/toy_ising_emergent_classicality.py to exist before export'
data = target_path.read_bytes()
payload = {
  'path': 'src/experiments/toy_ising_emergent_classicality.py',
  'size': len(data),
  'encoding': 'base64',
  'sha256': hashlib.sha256(data).hexdigest(),
  'content': None
}
if len(data) > 20000:
    compressed = gzip.compress(data)
    payload['encoding'] = 'gzip+base64'
    payload['content'] = base64.b64encode(compressed).decode('ascii')
else:
    payload['content'] = base64.b64encode(data).decode('ascii')

print('FILE_EXPORT:' + json.dumps(payload, separators=(',', ':')))
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
